Assuming there is the following constructor:

```
public IndexModel(int id)
{

}
```

You can right-click on `id` -> Quick Actions and Refactorings and you get the options
- Introduce and initialize property 'Id
- Introduce and initialize field '_id'

For regular methods, you don't have these options. Since a field is generated with readonly, this makes no sense, but for a property, this can be useful for Factory / Builder classes or if you work with method chaining.
Therefore I'd suggest to add the quick action Introduce and initialize property 'xy'.

Example:
```
public void Build(int id)
{
}
```

Would become
```
public int Id { get; set; }

public void Build(int id)
{
    Id = id;
}
```

